	<section id="changelog:service">
		<title>System services</title>

		<section id="changelog:service:mail">
			<title>Mail services</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
  					This update provides the new package univention-mail-dovecot which integrates the IMAP/POP3 server dovecot into the UCS mail stack (<u:bug>34839</u:bug> <u:bug>38884</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
  					dovecot has been updated to version 2.2.13. The update provides several bugfixes and enhancements (<u:bug>34839</u:bug> <u:bug>38475</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The UCR variable mail/cyrus/imap/allowplaintext to (dis)allow plain text passwords over non-TLS connections has been added. The variable defaults to "no".
					This changes the previous default behaviour! Plain text authentication over unencrypted connections is now disabled by default. To revert to the old behaviour set mail/cyrus/imap/allowplaintext=yes resp.  mail/dovecot/imap/allowplaintext=yes (<u:bug>38500</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The UDM module policies/mailquota has been moved to the package univention-mail-cyrus. The UDM module will only be available if the UCS mail stack with cyrus is installed (<u:bug>38473</u:bug> <u:bug>39004</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Postfix will no longer resolve address mappings (e.g. BCC) before handing them over to amavis for content scanning if an archive folder has been defined (<u:bug>14619</u:bug> <u:bug>38884</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					To configure the max. number of concurrent Amavis processes, a new UCR variable has been introduced: mail/antivir/max_servers. When unset, the current default "2" is used (<u:bug>37653</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Add options to check IP-FQDN-mapping as a means to fight spam. Adds two new UCR variables: mail/postfix/smtpd/restrictions/sender/reject_unknown_client_hostname and mail/postfix/smtpd/restrictions/sender/reject_unknown_reverse_client_hostname for weaker and stricter reverse DNS checking respectively (<u:bug>38292</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

