	<section id="changelog:win">
		<title>Services for Windows</title>
		<section id="changelog:win:samba">
			<title>Samba</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Samba has been upgraded to version 4.2.3 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
 					The list of groups in the Kerberos PAC_LOGON_INFO now also contains the RID of primary group, this fixes GPO security filtering for primary group membership (<u:bug>37101</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
 					Huawei Unified Storage System S5500 V3 failed to join Samba AD domains (<u:bug>38827</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A coding error in the Samba implementation of the BACKUPKEY serverwrap protocol may cause problems with retrieving saved passwords on Windows clients (DPAPI). This issue has been fixed (<u:bug>39025</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					This update adds support for the default profile directory paths of Windows 8, 8.1 and 10. For new users they will now be created automatically on first logon (<u:bug>38643</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The ldb library and tools have been upgraded to version 1.1.20 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The talloc library has been upgraded to version 2.1.2 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The tdb library and tools have been upgraded to version 1.3.6 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The tevent library has been upgraded to version 0.9.25 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The package univention-ldb-modules has been rebuilt to match the new Samba version 4.2.3 (<u:bug>37939</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>
